ceTCGAtools

1. Introduction

ceTCGAtools is designed for ceRNA identification via integrative analysis of long-non coding RNA, protein coding gene, and miRNAs in TCGA https://gdc.cancer.gov/.

2. Set up environment

setwd('~/Documents/Research/Cancer_Genomics/Data/Bladder/ceTCGA/LinuxTest/')
source('~/Documents/Research/Cancer_Genomics/Data/Bladder/ceTCGA/ceRNA_functions.R')
load('~/Documents/Research/Cancer_Genomics/Data/Bladder/ceTCGA/ceDa.RData')

3. RNAseq data

3.1 Download RNAseq data

project <- 'TCGA-PRAD'
dataType <- 'RNAseq'
directory <- 'PRAD/RNAseq'
method='custom'
manifest='PRAD/RNAseq.gdc_manifest.2017-09-29T22-15-57.873377.txt'

####### download RNAseq data
downloadRNAFun(method=method, project=project, dataType = dataType, manifest=manifest, directory=directory)
## [1] "exists 551 files !"

3.7 Differential expression analysis

group <- factor(metaMatrix.RNA$sample_type)
group[1:7]
## [1] PrimaryTumor PrimaryTumor PrimaryTumor PrimaryTumor PrimaryTumor
## [6] PrimaryTumor PrimaryTumor
## Levels: PrimaryTumor SolidTissueNormal
design <- model.matrix(~0+group)
head(design)
##   groupPrimaryTumor groupSolidTissueNormal
## 1                 1                      0
## 2                 1                      0
## 3                 1                      0
## 4                 1                      0
## 5                 1                      0
## 6                 1                      0
colnames(design) <- sapply(colnames(design), function(v) gsub('group| ','', v))
head(design)
##   PrimaryTumor SolidTissueNormal
## 1            1                 0
## 2            1                 0
## 3            1                 0
## 4            1                 0
## 5            1                 0
## 6            1                 0
contrast.matrix <- makeContrasts(PrimaryTumor-SolidTissueNormal, levels=design)
contrast.matrix
##                    Contrasts
## Levels              PrimaryTumor - SolidTissueNormal

DEGAll <- deAnalysisFun(v=v, design = design, contrast.matrix = contrast.matrix)

3.8 Volcano plot

volcanoPlotFun(DEGAll)

3.9 Extract DEGs

### All DEGs
deALL <- getDEFun(DEGAll = DEGAll, geneType = 'all')
dim(deALL)
## [1] 1546    8
#### DE long-noncoding
deLNC <- getDEFun(DEGAll = DEGAll, geneType = 'long_non_coding')
dim(deLNC)
## [1] 134   8
#### DE protein coding genes
dePC <- getDEFun(DEGAll = DEGAll, geneType = 'protein_coding')
dim(dePC)
## [1] 1368    8

3.10 Barplot

barPlotFun(de=deALL, angle=45, type='RNAseq')
